The course provides an overview of the basic research methods and the different forms of conducting studies in social sciences. The course shall explore the principles for conducting interviews, surveys, questionnaires and document analysis as well as the analysis methods of the data collected.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at providing students with theoretical knowledge and practical skills related to the research and analysis methods applied in the field of social sciences.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student will: 1) know the different stages of the research process and plan their research in accordance with ethical requirements; 2) have basic knowledge of data collection and analysis methods; 3) collect and analyse different data and interpret the results.
